		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yup, I'm concerned about the same thing.  The NSF aspect may actually warrant the need to discuss with an actual IP/DMCA attorney.  Tricky subject, I think, considering they're &quot;partial&quot; extractions (certainly containing original playerback code, sequenced data, and (if applicable) PCM samples)... but they're not &quot;an entire ROM&quot; in the literal sense.<br /><br />Bare minimum: Nintendo seems to be going after stuff they themselves produced, so NSFs of official Nintendo titles might be worth pulling, if there are any.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
