	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />NSF rips are 100% a copyright infringement either way, I don't think there's much to argue about that.<br /><br />The harder question is how much risk is involved in having them hosted on this forum, and to whom that risk belongs. It's been really weird to me that IP owners <em>don't</em> seem to police NSFs, VGM rips, etc. but as someone who enjoys and benefits from their presence I'm glad it's been this way.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


